"Woman Spy Case" Touted by Lee Myung Bak Group Dismissed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland issued a statement Tuesday slamming the Lee Myung Bak group for frantically kicking up a confrontational racket against the DPRK after cooking up what it called "woman spy case" in recent days. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The case does not deserve even a passing note as it is a threadbare charade disclosing the true aim sought by the group from the outset, but we can not but reveal the falsity of the case before the world as its orchestrator has gone far beyond the tolerance limit in a bid to hurt the dignity of the DPRK and tarnish its international image. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As far as the "woman spy" at issue is concerned, she is a criminal who fled after committing crimes against the state and the people, and human scum crazy for money, vanity and swindling. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She finished middle school education, enjoying free education and free medical care in the DPRK but after school she was engrossed in fraud, swindling and theft to meet even legal punishment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She did not reform herself even in the subsequent period but continued swindling. She defected to the south long ago, evading punishment by law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the DPRK she not only did enormous damage to properties of the state and society but caused huge damage to private properties on several occasions. For these crimes she was sentenced to six years of forced labor and prison terms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As for her step-father whom the group claims was put under custody, he is also human scum who betrayed the homeland and the people. He idled away time while changing his jobs dozens of times when he was in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The puppets painted such swindlers and idlers as "spies dispatched by a certain institution of the north". This is ridiculous enough to make even a cat laugh. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The information about the activities allegedly conducted by the "woman spy" released by the puppet security authorities, is also a sheer lie.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said they hired the "woman spy" as a "security lecturer" at a unit of the puppet army despite the fact that they found something "questionable" in her from three years ago. This proves that the puppet army and the security authorities of the south side must be made up of blind and deaf people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A lot of "spy cases" were cooked up in the south in the past, too, to spark off public furor, but this is the first time that such a clumsy "spy case" was fabricated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The farce orchestrated by the Lee group, not feeling ashamed of itself, only to become a laughing stock of the world is aimed to divert elsewhere the people's criticism of it due to its domestic and foreign policy failures and mislead the public opinion in a bid to get rid of the tight corner at which it is now finding itself. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is also aimed to rally conservative forces, suppress progressive forces, evade the responsibility for bedeviling the north-south relations and pursue confrontational policy towards fellow countrymen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The group of traitors has gone the lengths of painting such human scum little different to psychopath who has been engrossed in swindling, brokerage and prostitution as a "spy" and using her for the anti-DPRK confrontational racket. This clearly proves in what deplorable position the group is now finding itself. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fabrication of the case is another grave provocation to the DPRK in the wake of the incident of the south Korean tourist that took place in the area of Mt. Kumgang in July. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The group even tried to build up public opinion, groundlessly linking the "spy case" with the sacred institution in charge of the state security defence in the DPRK. This is an insult and mockery of the dignity and system of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will never remain an on-looker to the smear campaign against it launched by the group of traitors in a bid to do harm to the system in the DPRK after fabricating the above-said case, not content with deteriorating the inter-Korean relations while letting loose a spate of provocative outbursts inciting confrontation with fellow countrymen and crying out for "regime change" and "preemptive attack".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The recent incident more clearly proves that the Lee Myung Bak group is made up of philistines and anti-reunification confrontational maniacs putting the preceding military fascist dictators into the shade. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Traitor Lee Myung Bak seems to try to use the trite methods used by the preceding dictators in the past, not knowing how much the world has changed over the past decade. He should bear in mind that this is little short of following in the footsteps of the predecessors who met deaths.

Kim Yong Nam Receives Credentials from Cypriot Ambassador 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, received credentials from Marios P. Ieronymides, Cypriot ambassador to the DPRK, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there was Kung Sok Ung, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After receiving the credentials, Kim had a talk with him.

South Korean Authorities' Suppression of Pro-Reunification Figure under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Youth and Students Sub-Committee of the North Side Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration issued a statement on September 2 accusing the south Korean puppet authorities of taking such fascist action as sentencing Yun Ki Jin, chairman of the South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification, to three years in prison and three years of suspension of civil rights at a trial held on August 27 by invoking the ill-famed "National Security Law".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Lee Myung Bak group has forced Yun to undergo all sorts of mental and physical sufferings after arresting him in February last and inflicted heavy penalty upon him by bringing charges of "infiltration and escape," "accession to an enemy-benefiting organization" and "encouragement and praise," the statement noted, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They inflicted such heavy penalty upon him, not content with imposing all sorts of hardships upon him who was forced to live separated from his parents and wife and children for such a long period, after incriminating his activities for national unity and reunification on the charge of the violation of the NSL, an anti-human rights law, which has lost any justification to exist any longer. This rash act can be perpetrated only by the ferocious gang of fascists bereft of elementary human rights and ethics and morality and utterly indifferent to national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Lee group's suppression of Yun clearly revealed once again that they are fascist dictators and the group of anti-reunification elements who have not an iota of will to implement the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fascist suppression is not an all-powerful means for staying in power but a shortcut to destruction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Traitor Lee Myung Bak should behave himself, facing up to the trend of the history of the nation in which the Koreans are advancing to achieve unity and reunification by their concerted efforts under the banner of the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The puppet authorities should stop at once the suppression of the reunification movement organizations and immediately set free the unreasonably detained youth and students and figures including Yun.

Art Performance Marks Birthday of DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- A performance was given by the Workers' Art Group of the Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea (GFTUK) at the Central Workers' Hall on Sept. 2 on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance began with chorus "Song of the Proclamation of the People's Republic".  Put on the stage were colorful numbers such as trio poem recital "Immortal Feats" and mixed duet "Let's Sing of General Dear to People." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers sang high praises of the brilliant feats performed by President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Suk, an anti-Japanese war hero, in founding the DPRK, which demonstrates its dignity for being independent in politics, self-supporting in economy and self-reliant in national defence, and achieving its prosperity and the immortal exploits Kim Jong Il has performed by defending the socialist country with his original Songun politics and bringing about the dawn of a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their repertoire also included numbers reflecting the firm resolution of the workers to hold Kim Jong Il, the destiny of the country and the nation and a banner for winning victories, in high esteem with pure conscience and the noble sense of obligation and to work hard for the prosperity of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was appreciated by Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, officials of trade unions and members of trade unions in Pyongyang.

National Oratorical Meeting Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- A national oratorical meeting took place at the Central Youth Hall on September 2 to celebrate the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants heard oratories titled " Flag of the Republic", "We Know That", "White Snow", "Our Mental Power", "Umbrella", "Country and Rice" and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers highly praised President Kim Il Sung who built the country of people, the first of its kind in the history spanning 5,000 years by embodying the idea of believing in people as in Heaven and the immortal exploits General Secretary Kim Jong Il performed by bringing about a great heyday of national prosperity with his outstanding Songun revolutionary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The oratories reinforced the confidence of its participants that the DPRK would always emerge victorious, flying its national flag under the leadership of Kim Jong Il, Songun brilliant commander of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audience were Choe Thae Bok, Choe Yong Rim, leading officials of working people's organizations and working people in the city.  �@

National Art Exhibition Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- A national art exhibition for celebrating the 60th anniversary of the foundation of the DPRK was opened. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display at the exhibition are at least 700 art works depicting the undying exploits the three commanders of Mt. Paektu performed by founding and developing the DPRK and the KPA and the people dynamically advancing to bring about gigantic creations and changes and scale the eminence of a great prosperous powerful nation under the leadership of the Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Drawing the attention of visitors are Korean paintings "Helping people emerge masters of the state", "At the well side that conjures up memories of old days" and others portraying President Kim Il Sung who made indefatigable efforts to enable the Korean people to lead a genuine life as masters of the state and society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Oil painting "Visiting a post covered with snow" and other works impressively deal with the Songun leadership exploits of Kim Jong Il who has wisely led the struggle for defending the country and achieving its prosperity by paying endless visits to defence line posts and socialist construction sites. Also on display there are Korean painting "Wait for me please" and "Sharing joy over the first harvest" which depict the greatness of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk who devoted her all to achieving the national liberation and the cause of nation-building. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed there are works of diverse themes dealing with unforgettable events recorded in the six decade-long history of the DPRK including oil painting "Jaeryong Plain in the morning", jewel painting "We have nothing to desire more in the world," water-color painting "First patriotic donation of rice", woodcut " Okryu Restaurant animated with visitors" and calligraphic work "The country of people" and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its opening ceremony took place at the Pyongyang Indoor Stadium today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Minister of Culture Kang Nung Su made an opening speech.

Floral Basket and Greetings to Kim Jong Il 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a floral basket and a message of greetings by the economic and commercial councilors' corps here on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were conveyed to an official concerned by Cuban Commercial Councilor Enrique Gomez Soler, doyen of the above-said corps, on Wednesday. �@

Foreign Diplomats Visit Ryongmun Cavern 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- Officials in charge of cultural and friendly relations of different embassies here visited the Ryongmun Cavern on September 2 on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Being briefed on the fact that the Ryongmun Cavern unknown for ages came to boast its superb underground scenic beauty thanks to General Secretary Kim Jong Il's noble idea of believing in people as in Heaven and his wise leadership, the guests enjoyed magnificent, graceful, fascinating and fantastic scenery presented by the cavern. �@

Book and Photo Exhibition and Film Show Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- A book and photo exhibition and film show were held at the Pyongyang Cultural Exhibition on Wednesday for the economic and commercial councilors' corps here on the occasion of the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They looked round photos showing the 60-year-long glorious history of the DPRK that has covered the road of victory and glory under the wise leadership of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also walked round famous works of the President and Kim Jong Il and books introducing the politics, economy, culture, history and others of the DPRK before watching Korean documentary "Answer of Korea."  �@

Chongchun Street, Sports Complex
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- The Chongchun Street is a sports complex in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The street stretches north-south from Angol Flyover to Chilgol Flyover. On its right side there are the Sosan Football Stadium, the Handball Gymnasium, the Table-tennis Gymnasium, the Combat Sports Gymnasium, the Light Sports Gymnasium, the Badminton Gymnasium, the Swimming Gymnasium, a house for relieving fatigue, a restaurant for sportspersons and hotels and on the left side there are the Taekwon-Do Hall, the Weightlifting Gymnasium, the Basketball Gymnasium and the Volleyball Gymnasium suited to the geographical features. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The total plottage of the sports and public buildings in the street run into hundreds of thousands of square meters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Dozens of sports events can be held simultaneously at the gymnasiums. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
All the gymnasiums have many rooms including training rooms of various events, referee rooms, coach rooms and all necessary sports facilities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The street was completed on September 3, Juche 77 (1988). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Several hundred home and international sports games have been held there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Now the Chongchun Street plays a big role in developing sports of the country. �@

Plunder of Underground Resources by Japanese Imperialists in Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- The Japanese imperialists had committed most brutal state crimes of plundering Korea of heaps of her rich underground resources during their 40-odd years of colonial rule. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
From the first days of their occupation of Korea, the Japanese imperialists shaped predatory policies and made desperate efforts for their realization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
They, who had surveyed the distribution of mineral resources of Korea in an all-round way from 1911, promulgated "Korean Mining Act", a colonial evil law, in 1915 to ensure the monopolistic and large-scale predatory acts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The Japanese imperialists limited the development and management of mines by Koreans to the extreme and guaranteed unlimited advance of Japanese mining capitalists into Korea by "law", thus revealing their heinous intention to stifle the national mining industry and carry away abundant underground resources. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The Japanese mining industry thronged into Korea by taking advantage of the condition that Korea was reduced to a colony of Japan and the "Korean Mining Act" was enforced, and began to carry away underground resources in full earnest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
In order to afford convenience in the Japanese mining capitalists' unlimited predatory acts, the imperialists enacted a series of policies one after another and revised some provisions of the "Korean Mining Act" in 1916. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
And they abolished the import tax on coal cutting and iron-making facilities and others to ship into Korea facilities needed for the first-stage processing of iron and lead ores and other minerals on the spot. It ensured by law the plunder of mining resources in a more extensive way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
As a result, the national mining industry of Korea was trampled underfoot utterly and the Japanese monopoly capitalists boomed, favored by it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Having built smelteries in various places including Hungnam and Haeju, the Japanese imperialists resorted to every conceivable means to take away large amounts of nonferrous metals. During their occupation, they brought away nearly 400 tons of gold according to an extremely curtailed data. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
To fill the steel needed for the production of various kinds of weapons along with the escalation of the war of aggression, the Japanese imperialists developed iron ore mines in a big way and carried away iron ores. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Most of the iron works in Japan turned out iron with the iron ore which they carried away from Korea. Particularly, the iron works in Kyushu and Hokkaido were fed every year respectively with 200,000 tons and 40,000 tons of iron ore produced in Jaeryong, Unryul, Kaechon and other areas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Besides, they robbed Korea of precious mineral ores including zinc, nickel and magnesite. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The human history has witnessed lots of aggression and predatory acts. But it has not seen such an instance as the Japanese imperialist aggressors who plundered other country of underground resources in the most brigandish and vicious way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Japan is obliged to apologize and compensate for them. �@

DPRK Sure to Always Triumph
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- The 60-year-long history of the DPRK is a history in which it has always emerged victorious thanks to the might of the perfect unity between the leader and the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The path covered by the DPRK is a history in which it paved a unique path of socialism and has emerged victorious thanks to the might of the unbreakable unity between the leader and the people, a glorious history in which it created an ever-victorious heroic epic of the anti-imperialist struggle thanks to the might of this unity and a history in which it brought about epoch-making miracles and changes in the revolution and construction with the might of the above-said unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK's history is brilliantly shining as the epic of victory of the great unbreakable unity because it has held the peerlessly great man in high esteem as the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said harmonious whole symbolic of the dignity and might of the DPRK is based on the Korean people's unshakable faith in the greatness of President Kim Il Sung's idea and their absolute trust in his distinguished leadership ability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 60-year-long history of the DPRK is a sacred history which shines with the great idea and ever-victorious leadership of the President and his noble virtue of believing in people as in Heaven and the most brilliant history in which it set an example of the times in defending socialism and building a rich and powerful country thanks to the might of the above-said unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of the unbreakable unity between the President and the Korean people is given steady continuity thanks to General Secretary Kim Jong Il. The DPRK founded by the President will always triumph thanks to the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il and the single-minded unity of all servicepersons and people around the headquarters of the revolution, concludes the article. �@

Rodong Sinmun on Songun Politics
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- The Songun politics calls for putting forward the army, the main force in the confrontation with the imperialists, as the mainstay of the revolution and giving top priority to the military affairs to cope with any moves of the imperialists for aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Wednesday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The idea that the Songun politics serves as a political mode to be always held fast to as long as imperialists remain on earth and their moves for aggression persist is based on the scientific clarification of imperialism, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Aggression and war are the mode of existence of the imperialists and their principal job. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They spark off an arms race and create the danger of war, keen to beef up armed forces and step up arms expansion in a bid to realize their wild ambition to dominate the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historic and strategic position of the Songun politics can never change as long as imperialism exists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Invariable is the principle of revolution which calls for defending the sovereignty of the country and winning victory by dint of arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The socialist cause is a revolutionary cause to be accomplished generation after generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists are working hard to ignite wars of aggression against socialist countries, posing constant military threats to them while regarding them as a thorn in their flesh. They are, at the same time, persisting in their moves to destabilize and bring down socialism through capitalist ideological and cultural poisoning. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The practical experience of the people of the DPRK and the historic review of the Korean revolution prove that the Songun politics is the life and soul and future of the country and the nation and to advance under the uplifted banner of Songun provides a sure guarantee for winning victory in the popular masses' cause of independence, the socialist cause despite any storm and stress and hardships of history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The developing countries and small countries should direct bigger efforts to boosting their military capabilities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should not have any slightest illusion about imperialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should never be taken in by the imperialists' policy of "appeasement" but bolster up their defense capabilities as long as the imperialists exist. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The master key to frustrating the imperialists' policy of strength and achieving victory in the human cause of independence, the cause of peace lies in always holding fast to the Songun politics, the most effective and all-mighty treasured sword in the present era.

Buddhists' "Anti-Government" Actions Staged
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- Masses were simultaneously held in at least 10,000 temples across south Korea including Jogye Temple in Seoul on August 31 in protest against traitor Lee Myung Bak's religious discrimination, according to MBC of south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the masses excoriated Lee for still ignoring Buddhism and turning down even the demand for the dismissal of the chief of the Police Office even after Buddhists rose up in protest against the authorities' biased policy on religion on August 27. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They threatened to hold again all-Buddhists rallies across south Korea unless the authorities meet the demands of the Buddhist circle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  They strongly urged Lee to make an apology for the religious discrimination and fire the chief of the Police Office. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A video dealing with the present "government's" suppression of Buddhism was shown at the masses.

Struggle against Neo-liberalist Educational Policy Declared in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- The Teachers Union of south Korea held an extraordinary meeting of its deputies in Chungju City, North Chungchong Province, on August 30 and 31 at which it declared that the union would carry on the struggle against the neo-liberalist educational policy of the "government", according to CBS of south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The union accused the "government" of unilaterally pushing ahead with the neo-liberalist policy such as "forcing schools to teach students in English" and "school autonomy" in defiance of people's opinion which would seriously affect education. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The union declared that it would stage dynamic actions to force the present "government" to set right the wrong educational policy

Abolition of NSL Demanded in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- The Action Headquarters of the 16th-term south Korean Federation of University Student Councils on August 29 issued a statement demanding the abolition of the "National Security Law (NSL)", a fascist law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement recalled the fact that the Seoul Central District Court on August 27 held a trial at which it sentenced the chairman of the South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification to a prison term on the charge of "violence of the NSL".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It noted that the court, justifying the NSL in the course of the trial, totally denied the progress made in the development of the inter-Korean relations since the publication of the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement charged that since Lee Myung Bak came to power the number of victims of the NSL has increased at an exponential rate and his brutal crackdown upon the progressive forces is getting more undisguised than ever before. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that all the south Koreans are calling for the repeal of the NSL, the statement warned that the Lee group's intensified crackdown upon the progressive forces would touch off stronger resistance. �@

Rally for Reunification Held in Seoul
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- A rally for reunification in 2008 took place in Seoul on Aug. 30 with an attendance of members of more than 20 political parties and organizations and school youth and children. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the rally called for grasping once again the significance of the June 15 joint declaration and October 4 declaration and actively turning out to implement them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said that the above-said rally would provide the inhabitants in the area with an opportunity to show greater interest in national reunification and lay a cornerstone for achieving peaceful reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They expressed their will to expand the reunification movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The event included a photo exhibition on the north, an art performance and primary schoolers' competition in drawing paintings on the theme of reunification. �@

Kim Jong Il's Work Published in Austria
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il's famous work "Our Socialism Centred on the Masses Shall Not Perish" was brought out in pamphlet by the Joseph Gebauer Publishing House in Vienna, Austria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work, published on May 5, Juche 80 (1991), clarifies the inevitability of the victory of socialism, the solidity and the secret of the invincibility and the intrinsic characteristics of socialism in the DPRK and others.

DPRK Praised by Guinean Figure
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- Banou Keita, chairman of the Guinea-Korea Friendship Association, issued a statement on August 25 on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said that the foundation of the DPRK on Sept. 9, 1948 was the fruition of the arduous and protracted struggle of the Korean people for national independence, adding that the six decade-long history of the DPRK is recorded with the struggle to safeguard and glorify its sovereignty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No wonder, the world public is becoming increasingly vocal praising the DPRK as a fortress of independence as it is dynamically advancing along the path chosen by itself with faith and grit, while resolutely reacting to the U.S. high-handed policy with the toughest measures, stressed the statement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It expressed belief that the Korean people would always exalt victory and glory in the struggle to defend the dignity of the country and nation under the banner of Songun. �@

DPRK's Birthday Marked in South Africa
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- The Mfumalanga Provincial Committee of the South African Communist Party and the South African Association of Friendship and Solidarity with Korean People jointly released a special bulletin on Aug. 28 on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin under the headline "60th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK" carried articles under various titles including "The DPRK and its founding father Kim Il Sung", "HE Kim Jong Il's Songun exploits shining in human history" and "Songun politics and Korean-style socialism".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin in its preface noted that the DPRK is a state which, founded by President Kim Il Sung, has won one victory after another thanks to the wise Songun politics of General Secretary Kim Jong Il and represents an ideal society of humankind in which all people live a harmonious and happy life, receiving enormous benefits unimaginable in other countries including free medical care and free education. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It stressed that over the past six decades since its foundation the DPRK has advanced straightly along the path of victory despite any worldwide upheaval as it has thoroughly embodied the Songun idea in all spheres of state activities, guided by the great Juche idea centered on man. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It praised Kim Jong Il as a great statesman who has achieved the strong unity and cohesion of all servicepersons and people with his unique Songun politics and wisely led the socialist cause by foiling the imperialists' moves to stifle the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Socialism winning one victory after another in the DPRK serves as a banner instilling enormous strength and courage into the world progressive people, it emphasized. �@�@�@

Birthday of DPRK to Be Marked in Equatorial Guinea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 3 (KCNA) -- An inaugural ceremony of the Equatorial Guinean preparatory committee to celebrate the 60th birthday of the DPRK was held in Malabo on Aug. 26. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the ceremony the vice-minister of Education, Science and Sports of Equatorial Guinea was elected chairman of the preparatory committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The committee decided to conduct various political and cultural events on the occasion. �@

CRPP denuncia invencion de "caso de espia" de banda de Lee Myung Bak
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 3 de septiembre (ATCC) -- El portavoz del Comite por la Reunificacion Pacifica de la Patria (CRPP) hizo publica el dia 2 una declaracion denunciando a la banda de Lee Myung Bak que invento el "caso de espia" contra la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y arma campana de  confrontacion con esta. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El presente caso es una farsa fraudulenta que se  puso al desnudo su naturaleza desde el principio y no tiene nada de valor de hablar. Pero, dado que con esta farsa la banda de Lee dana la dignidad de la RPDC y denigra hasta su imagen exterior, nos vimos obligados a aclarar la falsedad del caso, senala el documento y continua: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La "espia" en cuestion es la delincuente que se fugo por su crimen cometido ante el Estado y el pueblo y es una escoria humana enloquecida por el dinero, deformacion y fraudes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Bajo el sistema de educacion gratuita y asistencia medica gratuita de la RPDC, ella recibio la ensenanza media y se incorporo a la sociedad. Pero,  al cabo de ocuparse de fraudes, estafas y robos recibio debidamente la sancion legal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Sin embargo, en vez de arrepentirse de su proceder, no ceso de cometer actos fraudulentos y hace mucho tiempo paso ilegalmente la frontera y despues, paso al Sur de Corea evadiendo la sentencia legal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Cuando vivia en la RPDC, robo en varias ocasiones la enorme suma de los bienes estatales, sociales e individuales, debido a lo cual fue condenada a 6 anos de trabajos reeducativos y debio sufrir la vida carcelaria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
El llamado padrastro de la "espia", que fue detenido junto con ella, es tambien un holgazan que cambio decenas veces de sus empleos sin tener la profesion fija y se huyo al Sur de Corea al traicionar la patria y el pueblo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Es muy ridiculo que los titeres surcoreanos  hicieron de tales tipejos los "espias enviados por un organo correspondiente del Norte".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Son mentirosos los datos de actividades de la "espia" publicados por las autoridades titeres de seguridad publica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
